00:43:08.532 --> 00:43:12.040
INTERPRETER: In terms of
particularly in relation

00:43:12.040 --> 00:43:17.930
to past and future lives,
within the realm of Buddhism

00:43:17.930 --> 00:43:22.820
there is a great amount of
evidence concerning this.

00:43:22.820 --> 00:43:25.300
So not just only the
recollections and memories

00:43:25.300 --> 00:43:29.380
of people, but
also, in many cases,

00:43:29.380 --> 00:43:32.010
people are able to
prove they've got

00:43:32.010 --> 00:43:35.040
physical evidence of
actions and activities

00:43:35.040 --> 00:43:39.840
that they have conducted
in previous lives, too.

00:43:39.840 --> 00:43:41.720
So from a Buddhist
point of view,

00:43:41.720 --> 00:43:44.160
from a religious
point of view, this

00:43:44.160 --> 00:43:46.420
is-- there is a lot of evidence.

00:43:46.420 --> 00:43:50.600
However, this is
something that remains

00:43:50.600 --> 00:43:55.000
very difficult for science
to research seriously

00:43:55.000 --> 00:43:57.409
using its current methods.

00:43:57.409 --> 00:44:00.420
KHENPO TSULTRIM LODRO:
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:44:20.115 --> 00:44:23.130
INTERPRETER: So for example
in Tibetan Buddhism,

00:44:23.130 --> 00:44:26.540
in the case of
treasure revealers

00:44:26.540 --> 00:44:31.640
who discover treasures that
were planted in previous lives,

00:44:31.640 --> 00:44:35.260
this is precisely
the kind of activity

00:44:35.260 --> 00:44:39.620
that involves treasure
revealers tapping into knowledge

00:44:39.620 --> 00:44:40.760
from previous lives.

00:44:40.760 --> 00:44:43.360
So this is one type
of evidence that

00:44:43.360 --> 00:44:47.905
is regarded as valid from
a religious point of view.

00:44:47.905 --> 00:44:49.890
KHENPO TSULTRIM LODRO:
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:45:01.042 --> 00:45:04.710
INTERPRETER: Khenpo feels
that if the existence

00:45:04.710 --> 00:45:09.010
of past and future lives
was able to be understood

00:45:09.010 --> 00:45:12.470
and therefore able to be
accepted, that this would open

00:45:12.470 --> 00:45:15.930
up a great scope for
doing further research

00:45:15.930 --> 00:45:21.050
into other aspects or
other aspects of the mind

00:45:21.050 --> 00:45:24.034
existing beyond the body.

00:45:24.034 --> 00:45:27.330
KHENPO TSULTRIM LODRO:
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:46:01.352 --> 00:46:03.270
INTERPRETER: For
example, in the--

00:46:03.270 --> 00:46:06.400
in terms of treasure
revealing, Khenpo

00:46:06.400 --> 00:46:09.760
has seen with his own
eyes-- and not just himself,

00:46:09.760 --> 00:46:13.160
but many have seen with
their own eyes-- for example,

00:46:13.160 --> 00:46:19.126
Khenpo's own teacher actually
go about revealing treasures,

00:46:19.126 --> 00:46:23.230
so recovering treasures from
lakes and from other places,

00:46:23.230 --> 00:46:27.640
as well, revealing--
taking out vessels or items

00:46:27.640 --> 00:46:31.340
and opening them and finding
within them pieces of paper

00:46:31.340 --> 00:46:33.100
on which symbols were written.

00:46:33.100 --> 00:46:35.620
And this kind of
action is very much

00:46:35.620 --> 00:46:38.620
one that is based on
a consciousness that

00:46:38.620 --> 00:46:43.150
transcends the body and
connects past lifetimes

00:46:43.150 --> 00:46:44.370
to the present lifetime.

00:46:44.370 --> 00:46:46.520
So Khenpo feels that
this is something,

00:46:46.520 --> 00:46:48.700
if properly
investigated, would yield

00:46:48.700 --> 00:46:51.694
a lot of useful information.

00:46:51.694 --> 00:46:53.780
KHENPO TSULTRIM LODRO:
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:47:08.020 --> 00:47:12.350
INTERPRETER: Khenpo feels that
a research methodology that

00:47:12.350 --> 00:47:15.700
relies primarily on
researching the brain

00:47:15.700 --> 00:47:20.030
to understand consciousness is
an extremely narrow and limited

00:47:20.030 --> 00:47:22.380
approach from the point
of view that we still

00:47:22.380 --> 00:47:24.090
don't understand the brain.

00:47:24.090 --> 00:47:27.230
So if we're using an organ that
we don't yet fully understand

00:47:27.230 --> 00:47:29.180
to understand this
kind of thing,

00:47:29.180 --> 00:47:32.910
then it seems from the outset
that it's quite limited.

00:47:32.910 --> 00:47:36.380
KHENPO TSULTRIM LODRO:
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:48:10.830 --> 00:48:14.310
INTERPRETER: Another example
is near-death experiences,

00:48:14.310 --> 00:48:17.110
which is something that Khenpo
has also done a bit of research

00:48:17.110 --> 00:48:21.500
into, as well, where people
who have such an experience,

00:48:21.500 --> 00:48:24.530
their consciousness leaves
their body for a period of time

00:48:24.530 --> 00:48:27.330
and, during the period
that it has left the body,

00:48:27.330 --> 00:48:32.550
does various things and is
effective in various ways.

00:48:32.550 --> 00:48:37.270
This is something that there
is quite clear-- or there's

00:48:37.270 --> 00:48:40.710
a lot of evidence for, and
that is possible to understand

00:48:40.710 --> 00:48:42.246
quite clearly.

00:48:42.246 --> 00:48:45.152
KHENPO TSULTRIM LODRO:
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:48:50.300 --> 00:48:52.620
INTERPRETER: Do
you think-- what's

00:48:52.620 --> 00:48:54.680
your opinion about
near-death experience?

00:48:54.680 --> 00:48:59.194
Do you think it is
something that's true?

00:48:59.194 --> 00:49:00.290
DAVID PRESTI: Yes.

00:49:00.290 --> 00:49:03.960
And I also believe
that that is one

00:49:03.960 --> 00:49:09.730
of the other very powerful
places where we can investigate

00:49:09.730 --> 00:49:15.230
empirically things that are
happening with consciousness

00:49:15.230 --> 00:49:17.440
that are currently
not explicable.

00:49:17.440 --> 00:49:20.550
If it can be
empirically verified

00:49:20.550 --> 00:49:24.870
by what people are saying,
that their awareness has

00:49:24.870 --> 00:49:27.330
left their body for
a period of time

00:49:27.330 --> 00:49:30.220
and experienced this or that
and then comes back and then

00:49:30.220 --> 00:49:31.600
that's empirically verified.

00:49:31.600 --> 00:49:34.620
And there are people who are
attempting to do that-- again,

00:49:34.620 --> 00:49:38.230
a very small number--
and it's good science.

00:49:38.230 --> 00:49:41.470
It's just so hard to do
these kinds of projects

00:49:41.470 --> 00:49:45.210
because scientists
like to set up things

00:49:45.210 --> 00:49:49.780
that they can reproduce in some
nice, neat way in a laboratory.

00:49:49.780 --> 00:49:52.401
You can't do that with
a near-death experience,

00:49:52.401 --> 00:49:52.900
you know?

00:49:52.900 --> 00:49:56.220
They're very-- they
have their own agenda.

00:49:56.220 --> 00:49:58.108
[LAUGHTER]

00:49:59.020 --> 00:50:00.930
You know, I just
want to say that I'm

00:50:00.930 --> 00:50:06.970
very optimistic about the
future of this encounter

00:50:06.970 --> 00:50:08.930
between these
traditions, and where

00:50:08.930 --> 00:50:13.460
this might lead for expanded
ways of appreciating

00:50:13.460 --> 00:50:15.349
the intricate activity
of all beings.

00:50:15.349 --> 00:50:17.140
KHENPO TSULTRIM LODRO:
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:50:34.390 --> 00:50:36.600
INTERPRETER: Khenpo
also feels that,

00:50:36.600 --> 00:50:40.080
for the future collaboration
between Buddhist researchers

00:50:40.080 --> 00:50:44.510
and practitioners between--
in terms of collaborations

00:50:44.510 --> 00:50:47.550
between them and
scientists, he also

00:50:47.550 --> 00:50:51.550
feels extremely optimistic
about the potential here.

